  "issue_title": "[Bug] PatBroadcastSynapse leaks miner GitHub PAT through repr()/str()",
  "issue_body": "### Summary\n\n`PatBroadcastSynapse.github_access_token` is a vanilla pydantic field with no `repr=False` and no `__repr__` override. Both `repr(synapse)` and `str(synapse)` emit the full GitHub PAT in plaintext, so any `bt.logging.debug(synapse)`, uncaught-exception traceback that includes the synapse, or log-shipper that captures stdout will leak every miner's PAT to disk and downstream log infrastructure.\n\n### Reproduction\n\n```python\nfrom gittensor.synapses import PatBroadcastSynapse\n\ns = PatBroadcastSynapse(github_access_token='ghp_SUPERSECRET12345')\nprint(repr(s))\n# PatBroadcastSynapse(github_access_token='ghp_SUPERSECRET12345', accepted=None, rejection_reason=None)\nprint(str(s))\n# github_access_token='ghp_SUPERSECRET12345' accepted=None rejection_reason=None\n```\n\n### Why this matters\n\n- Validators receive PATs from every registered miner. A single `bt.logging.debug(synapse)` or an exception handler that logs the synapse object compromises every miner that has broadcast.\n- Once a PAT lands in a log file (rotated, shipped to a SaaS, captured in a `docker logs` dump), recovery requires every miner to rotate their GitHub token.\n- The codebase already treats this field as sensitive \u2014 `pat_handler.py` zeroes `synapse.github_access_token = ''` after save ([line 73](gittensor/validator/pat_handler.py#L73)) and in the blacklist path ([line 41](gittensor/validator/pat_handler.py#L41)). That defensive zeroing only protects the response path; if anything raises between `validate_github_credentials` and the clearing, error handlers that log the synapse leak the token.\n\n### Affected file\n\n- [`gittensor/synapses.py:7-21`](gittensor/synapses.py#L7-L21)\n\n### Proposed fix\n\n1. Mark `github_access_token` with `Field(repr=False)` so pydantic's default `repr` excludes it.\n2. Override `__repr__` / `__str__` to render `***<last 4 chars>` instead of the raw token.\n3. Keep `model_dump_json()` / wire serialization unchanged \u2014 the token must still transmit over the (HTTPS) axon channel.\n\n```python\nfrom pydantic import Field\n\nclass PatBroadcastSynapse(bt.Synapse):\n    github_access_token: str = Field(repr=False)\n    accepted: Optional[bool] = None\n    rejection_reason: Optional[str] = None\n\n    def __repr__(self) -> str:\n        token = self.github_access_token or ''\n        masked = f'***{token[-4:]}' if len(token) >= 4 else '***'\n        return (\n            f'PatBroadcastSynapse(github_access_token={masked}, '\n            f'accepted={self.accepted!r}, rejection_reason={self.rejection_reason!r})'\n        )\n\n    __str__ = __repr__\n```\n\n### Tests\n\nAdd `tests/test_synapses.py` covering:\n\n- `repr(syn)` does not contain the raw token.\n- `str(syn)` does not contain the raw token.\n- `repr(syn)` keeps the last 4 chars (so operators can correlate masked log lines with rotated tokens).\n- Short tokens (< 4 chars) are fully masked \u2014 no `IndexError`.\n- Empty token does not crash `repr`.\n- `model_dump_json()` still includes the full token (wire format unchanged).\n",
  "merged_at": "2026-05-08T22:18:26.000Z",
